	(text_box "This project serves as a practice exercise in PCB design and embedded programming.\n\nThe result is a device that can be powered either by a battery or via a USB connection.\nThe device is capable of recharging the battery through the USB interface.\n\nKey features of the device include:\n- Sample sensors for temperature and humidity\n- External flash memory to support firmware-over-the-air (FOTA) updates\n- A modem module that connects the main microcontroller to the internet via LTE CAT-M1\n- Support for both an external antenna and an integrated antenna\n\nA primary objective of this project is to minimize reliance on totalitarian states (e.g., China or Russia), on countries that support such states (e.g., India), and on countries that may be hostile (e.g., the United States).\nComponent sourcing should prioritize manufacturers that do not produce components in such countries.\nPreference should be given to suppliers and manufacturers based in democratic nations, such as Taiwan and Germany.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15.24 101.6 0)
		(size 129.54 148.5899)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
